cp|8|AT|
^B@2 ^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let me just briefly describe the difference between Regular Bergen and Reverse Bergen Raises. Most on BBO seem to play Reverse Bergen Raises. Basically, if you play Bergen raises, there are 3 kinds of raises you can make. You can make a preemptive raise (4-6), constructive raise (7-9), or limit raise (10-12). Those raises are all done with 4 card support. In both regular Bergen and reverse Bergen, 3 of partner's suit (3H on this hand), is a preemptive raise (4-6). |
PG| ***** 83 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2 ^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|3C and 3D are reserved for the other kind of raises. If you play regular Bergen 3C is the weaker of the 2 raises (7-9) and 3D the stronger (10-12). If you play reverse Bergen the two bids are simply reversed, so 3C is the stronger raise (10-12) and 3D the weaker raise (7-9). Since Ginny wanted to play regular, not reverse, Bergen, Marge's bid was 3C, since she has 7 points. |
PG| ***** 84 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BMovie Maker: ^*N|cp||at|Please review a good tutorial on Bergen Raises either from Howard's web site or from the BIL library.|
PG| ***** 85 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717 ^*N|cp||at|As to the play, again, it is a matter of finding the best line to not lose 5 tricks. Ginny has 4 sure losers, 1 club, 2 diamonds and 1 spade. The whole hand comes down to trying to play the spade suit for 1 loser, not 2. There are 2 possibilities. You can play one of us for a doubleton Ace. Say you play Mei ann for a doubleton Ace. You lead low towards the SK. When it wins you lead low towards your hand and put up the 6. But, that is a pretty low percentage play. The much higher percentage play is to play Mei ann for the Jack. |
PG| ***** 86 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717 ^*N|cp||at|So, if you like, you can lead a low spade towards the Queen. Whether that wins or loses, the next time you get in, you play a low spade intending to finesse the 10 if no honor appears. The reason for playing a low spade towards the Queen first is, in case Mei ann has a doubleton Jack, or I have a singleton honor, you eliminate the guess. But, most of the time it won't matter. However, at least if you play Mei ann for the Jack, you have a 50% chance of making the contract. 50% is better than 0%. Always give yourself some chance to make.|
